<paragraph id="8BAA6179DF1EFFE01EE289B82E8AFE66" blockId="25.[143,241,391,415]" box="[143,241,391,415]" pageId="25" pageNumber="1430">
<emphasis id="B961BD6BDF1EFFE01EE289B82E8AFE66" box="[143,241,391,415]" italics="true" pageId="25" pageNumber="1430">Remarks</emphasis>
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BAA6179DF1EFFE01EE289912CAEFDDF" blockId="25.[143,1103,430,550]" pageId="25" pageNumber="1430">According to the original description, this species is well defined by its characteristic colouration: body largely pale ochraceous to testaceous or pitch brown, pronotum unspotted, and each elytron with an oblique humeral band and a dark stripe along suture, also with deep punctures in subregular rows.</paragraph>
